---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import { translations } from "../i18n/translations";
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy â€” Edgar Valdez">
  <Header />
  <main class="legal">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: February 2026</p>

      <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
      <p>
        This privacy policy explains how Edgar Valdez ("I", "me", "my")
        handles information in connection with the website valdezdev.work and
        associated applications and services (collectively, the "Services"),
        including integrations with third-party social media platforms.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Information Collection</h2>
      <p>
        The portfolio website itself is a static site that does not directly
        collect personal data. However, when you use the Services that
        integrate with third-party platforms, the following information may be
        collected or accessed:
      </p>
      <h3>2.1 Information from OAuth Authentication</h3>
      <p>
        When you connect your social media accounts via OAuth, the Services
        may receive:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your account profile information (name, username, profile picture)</li>
        <li>Your email address (if provided by the platform)</li>
        <li>Authentication tokens (access tokens, refresh tokens) required to perform authorized actions</li>
        <li>Account identifiers used to associate your account with the Services</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>2.2 Information from Connected Platforms</h3>
      <p>
        Depending on the permissions you grant, the Services may access:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Content you create through the Services for publishing</li>
        <li>Publishing status and metadata (post IDs, timestamps, engagement metrics)</li>
        <li>Account-level information necessary for content publishing</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p>Information accessed through the Services is used exclusively to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Authenticate your identity and maintain your session</li>
        <li>Publish content to your connected social media accounts on your behalf</li>
        <li>Display the status of published content</li>
        <li>Provide and improve the functionality of the Services</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do <strong>not</strong> use your data for advertising, profiling,
        or any purpose unrelated to the core functionality of the Services.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Third-Party Platform Integrations</h2>
      <p>
        The Services integrate with the following platforms. Each integration
        accesses only the data necessary for its intended functionality:
      </p>

      <h3>4.1 Google APIs</h3>
      <p>
        The Services use Google APIs (OAuth 2.0 verified project: antplify-dev,
        Project ID: 1094847225705) to access Google services such as YouTube
        and Google Business Profile. The Services' use and transfer of
        information received from Google APIs adheres to the
        <a href="https://developers.google.com/terms/api-services-user-data-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Google API Services User Data Policy</a>, including the Limited Use requirements.
      </p>
      <p>Scopes requested are limited to content publishing and account management.</p>

      <h3>4.2 Instagram API (Meta)</h3>
      <p>
        The Services use the Instagram Graph API / Content Publishing API to
        publish content to your Instagram account. Data accessed includes your
        Instagram profile information and content publishing capabilities. Usage
        is governed by
        <a href="https://developers.facebook.com/terms/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Meta's Platform Terms</a> and
        <a href="https://www.facebook.com/privacy/policy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Meta's Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h3>4.3 TikTok API</h3>
      <p>
        The Services use the TikTok API to publish content to your TikTok
        account. Data accessed is limited to account information necessary for
        publishing. Usage is governed by
        <a href="https://www.tiktok.com/legal/terms-of-service" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          TikTok's Terms of Service</a> and
        <a href="https://www.tiktok.com/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          TikTok's Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h3>4.4 Twitter/X API</h3>
      <p>
        The Services use the Twitter/X API to publish content to your
        Twitter/X account. Data accessed is limited to account information
        necessary for publishing. Usage is governed by
        <a href="https://twitter.com/en/tos" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Twitter/X's Terms of Service</a> and
        <a href="https://twitter.com/en/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Twitter/X's Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h3>4.5 Cloudflare</h3>
      <p>This website is hosted on Cloudflare Pages, which may collect:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Basic web analytics (page views, country-level location data)</li>
        <li>Standard server logs (IP addresses, browser type, timestamps)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        For more information, see
        <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Cloudflare's Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Data Storage & Retention</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Authentication tokens</strong> are stored securely and retained only for as long as necessary to maintain your connection to the Services. Tokens are deleted when you disconnect your account.</li>
        <li><strong>Content data</strong> (text, media) that you submit for publishing is processed and transmitted to the target platform. It is not permanently stored by the Services after successful publishing.</li>
        <li><strong>Account information</strong> (username, profile data) is retained only while your account is connected to the Services.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>6. Data Sharing</h2>
      <p>
        I do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer any personal information
        to third parties. Data is only shared with the specific third-party
        platforms you have authorized (e.g., when publishing content to your
        Instagram account, your content is sent to Instagram's API).
      </p>

      <h2>7. Data Security</h2>
      <p>
        The Services implement the following security measures:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>HTTPS encryption via Cloudflare SSL/TLS for all communications</li>
        <li>OAuth 2.0 for secure authentication (no passwords are stored)</li>
        <li>Authentication tokens are stored securely and encrypted</li>
        <li>Minimum necessary permissions (scopes) are requested from each platform</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        While I strive to protect your information, no method of transmission
        over the Internet is 100% secure.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Your Rights & Choices</h2>
      <p>You have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Revoke access:</strong> Disconnect your social media accounts at any time through each platform's account settings or through the Services.</li>
        <li><strong>Request data deletion:</strong> Contact me to request deletion of any data associated with your account.</li>
        <li><strong>Access your data:</strong> Request a copy of the data the Services hold about you.</li>
        <li><strong>Withdraw consent:</strong> You may stop using the Services at any time.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        The Services are not directed at children under the age of 13. I do
        not knowingly collect any information from children. If you believe a
        child has provided data through the Services, please contact me
        immediately.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        This privacy policy may be updated from time to time. Changes will be
        reflected on this page with an updated revision date. We encourage you
        to review this page periodically.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For privacy-related questions, data requests, or concerns, please contact:
        <a href="mailto:contact@valdezdev.work">contact@valdezdev.work</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<script is:inline define:vars={{ translations }}>
  window.__translations = translations;
  if (window.__applyLang && window.__currentLang) {
    window.__applyLang(window.__currentLang);
  }
</script>
